<subSubSection id="3BF3651CD868FF83FF3AFEFCFE0BF745" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" type="description">
<paragraph id="73563697D868FF83FF3AFEFCFE0BF745" blockId="2.[134,773,285,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
<bibRefCitation id="17784B66D868FF83FF3AFEFCFE1AF525" author="Richardson, J" box="[134,439,285,308]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" pagination="187 - 320" refId="ref7180" refString="Richardson, J., 1846. Report on the ichthyology of the seas of China and Japan. Report of the British Association for the Advancement of Science for 1845: 187 - 320." type="journal article" year="1846">Richardson (1846: 258–259)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="B4E94D14D868FF83FD96FEFCFD66F525" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1846" box="[554,715,285,308]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Julis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exornatus">
<emphasis id="419DEA85D868FF83FD96FEFCFD66F525" box="[554,715,285,308]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Julis exornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from watercolour paintings by Chinese artists obtained by John Reeves, who resided in Canton, and from specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="0BFE7607D868FF83FF3AFE9CFEA4F585" box="[134,265,381,404]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
. Richardson described two colour varieties in detail from the paintings. 
<bibRefCitation id="17784B66D868FF83FE04FE7CFD2DF5A5" author="Whitehead, P" box="[440,640,413,436]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" pagination="191 - 233" refId="ref7306" refString="Whitehead, P. J. P., 1969. The Reeves collection of Chinese fish drawings. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Historical Series 3 (7): 191 - 233." type="journal article" year="1969">Whitehead (1969)</bibRefCitation>
reproduced many of the paintings in black and white from the Reeves Collection of Chinese Fish Drawings in the Natural History Museum in London. We reproduce here, as 
<figureCitation id="EBD22A12D868FF83FDEFFE1CFD3CF605" box="[595,657,509,532]" captionStart="Fig 2" captionStartId="2.[134,168,1577,1598]" captionTargetBox="[167,738,1225,1547]" captionTargetId="figure-670@2.[134,773,1225,1560]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig 2. Painting of Halichoeres exornatus Richardson (after Whitehead, 1969)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5342850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5342850/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, the first of two paintings used by Richardson for his 
<taxonomicName id="B4E94D14D868FF83FDFCFDFCFD4FF625" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1846" box="[576,738,541,564]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Julis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exornatus">
<emphasis id="419DEA85D868FF83FDFCFDFCFD4FF625" box="[576,738,541,564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Julis exornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as copied from the original by Whitehead (Pl. 24 C). Comparison is provided with the first author’s photograph (
<figureCitation id="EBD22A12D868FF83FD3BFDBCFD65F665" box="[647,712,605,628]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[134,171,2062,2083]" captionText="Fig. 3. Halichoeres nigrescens, BPBM 22058, male, 83 mm, Singapore (J. E. Randall)." pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) of a male specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="B4E94D14D868FF83FEE8FD9CFDFDF685" baseAuthorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[340,592,637,660]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Halichoeres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrescens">
<emphasis id="419DEA85D868FF83FEE8FD9CFDFDF685" box="[340,592,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Halichoeres nigrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="0BFE7607D868FF83FD25FD9CFCA8F685" box="[665,773,637,660]" name="Singapore" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Singapore</collectingCountry>
(BPBM 22058, 83 mm SL). Sadovy &amp; Cornish (2000: 207) reported 
<taxonomicName id="B4E94D14D868FF83FE94FD5CFE6CF6C5" baseAuthorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[296,449,701,724]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Halichoeres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrescens">
<emphasis id="419DEA85D868FF83FE94FD5CFE6CF6C5" box="[296,449,701,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">H. nigrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="0BFE7607D868FF83FE56FD5CFDC0F6C5" box="[490,621,701,724]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
as “the most abundant wrasse in shallow areas of corals and boulders in sheltered and exposed shores.” We confirm the treatment by Parenti &amp; Randall (2002) of 
<taxonomicName id="B4E94D14D868FF83FE7FFCFCFDCAF725" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1846" box="[451,615,797,820]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Julis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exornatus">
<emphasis id="419DEA85D868FF83FE7FFCFCFDCAF725" box="[451,615,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Julis exornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="B4E94D14D868FF83FF19FCDCFE32F745" baseAuthorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[165,415,829,852]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Halichoeres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrescens">
<emphasis id="419DEA85D868FF83FF19FCDCFE32F745" box="[165,415,829,852]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Halichoeres nigrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
